{"questionId":"14778","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>On her first day in a hospital, Kiri receives <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> milligrams (mg) of a therapeutic drug. The amount of the drug Kiri receives increases by the same amount, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>, each day. On the seventh day, she receives 21 mg of the drug, and on the eleventh day she receives 29 mg.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Kiri receives the drug for 30 days.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the total amount of the drug, in mg, that she receives.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {{S_{30}} = } \\right)\\frac{{30}}{2}\\left( {2 \\times 9 + \\left( {30 - 1} \\right) \\times 2} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>30</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>30</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>9</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>30</mn>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong><strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong> for substitution in the sum of an arithmetic sequence formula; <strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)</strong> for their correct substitution.</p>\n<p>1140&nbsp; (mg)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)<em>(G3)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span> from part (b).</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14778","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.T_4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the total amount of the drug, in mg, that she receives.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}